Key Match Events: Timberwolves guard Anthony Edwards was fouled from behind by Magic guard Kentavious Caldwell-Pope while driving to the basket.
Without key players Paolo Banchero, Jalen Suggs, and Franz Wagner, Orlando was overwhelmed by the starpower of the Timberwolves.
Julius Randle scored 23 points and Anthony Edwards scored 21 points for the Timberwolves.
Pre-Game Insights: The Magic had to wait at least one more game before the return of All-Star forward Paolo Banchero.
Paolo Banchero was out due to return to competition reconditioning.
Jalen Suggs was out due to a low back strain.
Franz Wagner was out due to a torn right abdominal muscle.
